{
  "texts": [
    "By recognising and structuring evidence, this paper points out areas that limit the impact of current approaches on practices.",
    "Drawing on practical examples and theoretical suggestions, we cluster the identified problems into five areas: (1) the overly abstract nature of RAI guidelines leaving room for diverging interpretations, (2) the problem of identifying, prioritising, and aligning values, (3) the difficulty of operationalising success and impact metrics, (4) the fragmentation of the AI development process, and finally, (5) the lack of internal advocacy and accountability.",
    "In a second step, this paper examines existing recommendations on how to overcome each of these obstacles.",
    "Through examining less common approaches to RAI, we are attempting to gain an overview of current attempts across a variety of disciplines, approaches, and schools of thought.",
    "This allows us to gain a more comprehensive awareness of potential solutions, as well as to understand the relationships between interventions and existing challenges."
  ]
}